Ï† : G \to \mathbb{R}
\begin{pmatrix} a & 0\\b&a\end{pmatrix}\to b/a
\mathbb{R}
G=\left\{\left(\begin{smallmatrix}a&0\\b&a\end{smallmatrix}\right):a,b\in\mathbb{R},a\ne0\right\}
A, B \in G
A = \begin{pmatrix} a & 0 \\b & a\end{pmatrix},\quad a\neq 0, \qquad B = \begin{pmatrix} c & 0\\ d & c\end{pmatrix},\quad  c\neq 0
\phi: G\to \mathbb R
\quad \phi(A) = b/a,\quad \phi(B) = d/c
\phi(AB) = \phi(A) + \phi(B)
AB = \begin{pmatrix} ac & 0\\bc+ad& ac\end{pmatrix}
\phi(AB) = \dfrac{bc + ad}{ac}
\phi(AB) = \dfrac{bc + ad}{ac} = \dfrac{bc}{ac} + \dfrac{ad}{ac} = \dfrac ba + \dfrac dc =\phi(A) +\phi(B)
